Female ( IBSP 24828 ):
Coloration pattern as in male. Total length 10.4 . Prosoma: 4.0 long, 3.9 wide. Opisthosoma: 6.4 long, 4.2 wide. Eye diameters: 0.30 , 0.32 , 0.22 , 0.30 ; interdistances: 0.20 , 0.10 , 0.40 , 0.40 , 0.20 , 0.16 . Leg measurements: I: 19.6 ( 5.4 , 2.4 , 5.3 , 5.0, 1.5 ); II: 22.1 ( 6.3 , 2.5 , 6.1 , 5.6 , 1.6 ); III: 14.9 ( 4.5 , 1.9 , 3.8 , 3.6 , 1.1 ); IV: 17.0 ( 5.1 , 1.8 , 4.3 , 4.4 , 1.4 ). Spination follows the generic pattern. Epigynum: epigynal field slightly longer than wide; median septum almost twice longer than wide (
Fig. 68
). Vulva: pp with 3–4 linearly arranged lobes; fd transversal slightly shorter than pp (
Figs 69–70
).

Distribution. Southeastern Atlantic Forest, only Serra do Mar in the state of São Paulo (
